metaData.descriptionCS: The examinee names letters of the alphabet, identifies and generates rhyming words, and completes other tasks deemed important for developing reading skills.

questions.title: Item 14. hat, mat, sun (sun)
questions.incorrectInstructionsHTML:
Incorrect response:

Say, When words rhyme, the sounds at the end of the words are the same. Say the words with me: hat, mat, sun. Hat and mat rhyme because they both end with \at\. So the word that does not rhyme with the others is sun. Let’s try another one.

questions.title: Item 15. fish, duck, dish (duck)
questions.topInstructionsHTML:
This time there are no pictures. Just listen. Fish, duck, dish. 

Which one does not rhyme with the others?

questions.title: Item 16. rhymes with fly
questions.topInstructionsHTML: Now, tell me a word that rhymes with fly.

scoreButtons.label: Any rhyming word / nonword (e.g., sky, kie)

questions.title: Item 17. rhymes with star
questions.topInstructionsHTML: Tell me a word that rhymes with star.

scoreButtons.label: Any rhyming word / nonword (e.g., far, lar)

questions.title: Item 18. bat, bike, truck (\b\–)
questions.incorrectInstructionsHTML:
Incorrect response:

Say, Bat and bike begin with the \b\ sound, but truck does not. Now you say bat and bike. Pause for the examinee to repeat the words.

questions.title: Item 24. \p\ \an\
questions.incorrectInstructionsHTML:
Incorrect response:

Say, Listen again: \p\ \an\. The word is pan.
questions.topInstructionsHTML: This time there are no pictures. I am going to say a word in two parts. Listen carefully to the parts, then put them together to make a word. (Pause for 1 second between the two word parts.) Listen: \p\ \an\. What is the word?

questions.title: Item 25. \m\ \op\
questions.topInstructionsHTML: Put these parts together to make a word. (Pause for 1 second between the two word parts.) Listen: \m\ \op\. What is the word?

questions.title: Item 26. \sh\ \ell\
questions.topInstructionsHTML: Put these parts together to make a word. (Pause for 1 second between the two word parts.) Listen: \sh\ \ell\. What is the word?
